<!-- Why switch -->
<section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
  <div class="lg:grid lg:grid-cols-2 lg:gap-12 lg:items-start">
    <div>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6">Why teams choose Enzyme over Slack</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">No per-seat pricing</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Slack's Pro plan starts at $7.25/user/month. For a 50-person team, that's over $4,000/year. Enzyme costs whatever your server costs — often under $10/month total.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Your data stays yours</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Every message, file, and conversation lives on your infrastructure. No third-party access, no data mining, no compliance headaches about where data is stored.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">No message history limits</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Slack's free tier limits searchable message history. Enzyme keeps everything — forever. It's your data on your server, why would it disappear?</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Open source and auditable</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Read every line of code that handles your messages. MIT licensed — no "open core" bait-and-switch where the features you need are behind a paywall.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-10 lg:mt-0 flex justify-center">
      <img src="/assets/illustrations/11.svg" alt="Illustration of a person thinking and evaluating options" class="w-full max-w-sm" width="384" height="265" loading="lazy" />
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

